		<hr size="1">Also when you compare earth/water pet you can notice something.  I actually might switch back to my 34 water pet over 34 earth because of how much the earth pet gets hit.  Comparitively the more times the earth pet gets hit and for how much more &gt; than the hp bonus he has over water pet.  add in that water pet does more dmg, the only reason i'd use earth over water is if the root was a must to prevent adds.  But when the earth pet roots, in the mobs last moments he is still inflicting dmg on the pet, where as a water pet chases the mob, inflicting dmg on it till its dead without taking any for the last 10%  of the fight.  The earth pet also takes more dmg, therefore, it takes more mana to heal him and thus costing you more downtime when soloing.  Water pets regen makes it so you have to heal less, and each heal will go farther when used on the water pet, cause earth pet's hp gets chewed up hehe. Sorry for long post</P><P>Mathezar 51 Pathfinder<BR>Zumin 34 Magician<BR>&lt;Guardians of the Dead&gt;<BR>Prexus server<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
