		</font>
		<hr size="1">As I leveled up, here are the rules I used for choosing which pet I was going to use:</P><P>1- Is a runner going to get me killed?  Then use Earth Pet in the hopes his root will prevent it.</P><P>2- Can the Fire pet handle the damage? Will he be the one taking the hits?  Then use him,  and make use of the nasty damage shield they cast upon themselves.</P><P>3- Am I going to fight a lot of casters, when the occaisional Stun will be handy?  Am I in  a group where the pet won't take much damage?  Then I use the Air pet.   </P><P>4- If all the above are not necessarily true, then I'll use the Water Pet. </P><P>--------------</P><P>You have to remember that the additional HP of the Earth pet are somewhat offset by the additional damage they'll take because the mob is rooted and cannot flee.  <br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
